.\" Manpage for Holberton Shell
.\" Contact for questions Grace Fallon or Derek Clemens on slack
.TH man 3 "15 Apr 2021" "1.0" "simple_shell man page"

.SH NAME
	simple_shell - a UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS

	simple_shell [no options]

.SH DESCRIPTION

	Simple_shell is a UNIX command line interpreter that executes commands recieved from STDIN.
.PP
.SH USAGE
.PP
	simple_shell accepts user commands from STDIN. The commmand is passed to the shell in the form of a string. the shell is capiable of the following:

	Tokenizing the command line string into a null terminated array.

	Searches the PATH for command if exact path is not given.

	Execute the command passed by the user.

	If the command or PATH are not found the simple_shell will return an error message.
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
	--help
.PP
     POC slack Grace Fallon or Derek Clemens

.SH ARGUMENTS
.PP
	simple_shell reads the first argument passed as a command, and the following arguments as command parameters.
.PP
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
	simple_shell can be accessed in 2 ways. interactive mode and non interactive mode.
.PP
.B	Interactive mode
.PP
        $ /bin/ls -l
.PP
.B	Non-ninteractie mode
.PP
	echo ls -l | ./hsh
.PP
.SH BUILTIN
.IP exit
Exits simple_shell and frees all memory allocated during use.

.SH BUGS
	No known bugs.

